title: Grateful Dead Live at Poplar Creek Music Theatre on 1983-06-27
lineage: Nakamichi CR-5A (24/96) > Tascam DR680|SD > i7Windows7          Audacity > cdwav editor > TLH flac level 8
taper: Tom Pinney & Kyle Holbrook and Executive Crew
description:
Set 1

Bertha-> Promised Land, Dupree's Diamond Blues, Minglewood Blues, Bird Song, Me & My Uncle-> Mexicali Blues, Cold Rain & Snow-> Hell In A Bucket-> Sugaree

Set 2

Scarlet Begonias-> Fire On The Mountain-> Estimated Prophet-> Truckin'-> Drums-> The Other One-> The Wheel-> Good Lovin', E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text:
35 years later My first Dead show. 15 years old and walking around the lot with the old invisible dog on a leash. Remember Jerry landing in the parking lot via helicopter and flashing us a big grin and a peace sign from the limo. He was wearing a white suit and carrying the briefcase of infinite felonies If I recall correctly. Remember the lady with the purse full of shrooms for sale. Think it rained later in the evening. Wonderful show, the beginning of a long strange trip leading up to show #100 at Lock'n.
Ain't no time to hate. (Sorry for not reviewing this recording - really enjoying the anniversary.) Stay well folks !
Great sound!!! The show speaks for itself, this Aud though is the best sounding one I've found here. Please Check it out.
